      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study with at least three mesh densities; discretization error estimated via Richardson extrapolation. GCI < 5% for all QoIs.",
      "rationale": "Three mesh densities (coarse, medium, fine) applied to the screw-rod-vertebral body assembly. Richardson extrapolation yielded GCI of 2.1% for stiffness and 3.4% for yield force. Fine mesh selected for production runs. Required level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative solver convergence verified; residual force norms below 0.1% of applied load at each increment.",
      "rationale": "Nonlinear quasi-static solver with arc-length control. Residual force norm confirmed below 0.05% of applied load at every converged increment. Required level 2 achieved."
