      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent review of model setup by a second analyst; documented simulation protocol followed.",
      "rationale": "Model setup reviewed by a second qualified analyst not involved in original construction. Discrepancies resolved and documented. Simulation protocol version-controlled in the project repository. Required level 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum FEA with elastic-plastic Ti-6Al-4V material model and frictional contact at screw-rod interface. Justification provided for all simplifying assumptions.",
      "rationale": "Bilinear isotropic hardening model calibrated to Ti-6Al-4V tensile data. Frictional contact (mu=0.2) at screw-rod and rod-block interfaces. UHMWPE vertebral body surrogate represented by linear elastic model consistent with ASTM F1717 protocol. All simplifications documented and justified. Required level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from coupon testing of same lot material; geometric inputs from CMM measurements of test specimens. Input uncertainty characterised via probability distributions.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V elastic modulus and yield strength obtained from coupon tensile tests on the same material lot as test constructs (n=6 coupons). Screw and rod geometry verified by CMM against nominal CAD. Input distributions (normal for modulus, lognormal for yield strength) assigned based on coupon variability. Uncertainty propagated through Monte Carlo sampling (n=500 runs) to generate predicted QoI distributions. A full sensitivity analysis to rank dominant input drivers is planned for a subsequent revision; the present assessment characterises aggregate output uncertainty without decomposing contributions by input factor. Required level 3 achieved.",
      "note": "UQ performed via Monte Carlo; sensitivity analysis to identify dominant input drivers is deferred to a future revision."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N=11 non-cannulated constructs from production lots; sample size sufficient to estimate mean and variability. Specimens representative of production population.",
      "rationale": "Eleven non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs assembled from production components. Constructs distributed across two independent laboratories to assess inter-laboratory reproducibility. Dimensional inspection confirmed all specimens within drawing tolerances. Required level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions replicate COU loading environment; multiple loading configurations or load levels tested.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed under ASTM F1717 static compression-bending at a single load configuration (5 mm/min crosshead displacement). Only one test condition evaluated; fatigue and torsion conditions not included in this validation activity. Achieved level 2 is below required level 3; this gap is acknowledged and constitutes a known limitation of the current validation scope."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA inputs (geometry, material, BCs) demonstrably equivalent to test specimen parameters; discrepancies quantified.",
      "rationale": "FEA geometry updated from CMM measurements of each specimen. Material inputs matched to coupon data from the same lot. Boundary conditions (grip displacement, fixture stiffness) replicated from laboratory protocol documentation. Residual discrepancies in fixture compliance quantified and incorporated into the validation uncertainty budget. Required level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (E/uval) computed for all QoIs; acceptance criterion E/uval < 1.96 pre-specified.",
      "rationale": "E/uval computed for stiffness (0.87), yield force (1.14), and force at 40 mm (1.52). All three QoIs satisfy the pre-specified criterion E/uval < 1.96. Relative errors also within the <10% bound. Required level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) directly linked to device performance requirements and clinical risk.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness governs load sharing with the vertebral column; yield force is the primary structural integrity metric; force at 40 mm characterises post-yield reserve. All three are specified in the device design requirements and directly relevant to the clinical use scenario. Required level 3 achieved."
    },
